
---


@startuml

' Actors
actor "Visitor" as Visitor
actor "User" as User
actor "Administrator" as Admin

' Use Cases
[Register] as UC_Register
[Confirm Email] as UC_ConfirmEmail
[Create Building] as UC_CreateBuilding
[Manage Entries] as UC_ManageEntries
[Comment] as UC_Comment
[Search Buildings] as UC_SearchBuildings
[Release Entry] as UC_ReleaseEntry
[Delete Comment] as UC_DeleteComment
[Set Up User] as UC_SetUpUser
[Activate User] as UC_ActivateUser

' Classes
class WebPortal {
    - versionNumber: String
    - url: String
    - buildings: Set<Building>
}

class Building {
    - id: String
    - name: String
    - energyClass: String (A/B/C/D)
    - address: String
    - constructionYear: Integer
    - owner: User
    - images: List<Image>
    - profilePhoto: Image
    - additionalEntries: List<AdditionalEntry>
}

class Image {
    - fileName: String
}

class AdditionalEntry {
    - name: String
    - content: Union<String, Float>
    - unit: String
    - isPublic: Boolean
}

class User {
    - username: String
    - email: String
    - password: String
    - activated: Boolean
    - buildings: Set<Building>
}

class Administrator extends User {
    - idCardNumber: String
}

' Relationships between classes
WebPortal "1" -- "many" Building : has
Building "1" -- "1" User : owned by
User "1" -- "many" Building : manages
Building "1" -- "many" Image : has
Building "1" -- "many" AdditionalEntry : has

' Use Cases and Actors
Visitor --> UC_SearchBuildings
Visitor --> UC_Register
Visitor --> UC_ConfirmEmail
User --> UC_CreateBuilding
User --> UC_ManageEntries
User --> UC_Comment
User --> UC_ReleaseEntry
Admin --> UC_SetUpUser
Admin --> UC_ActivateUser
Admin --> UC_DeleteComment

' Generalization
Administrator --|> User

@enduml

---

### 📌 **Explanation of Key Elements**

- **Actors**: `Visitor`, `User`, and `Administrator` represent different types of users interacting with the system.
- **Use Cases**:
  - `UC_Register`: For new users to register.
  - `UC_ConfirmEmail`: Verification step during registration.
  - `UC_CreateBuilding`: Users can create new buildings.
  - `UC_ManageEntries`: Users can add or modify entries for their buildings.
  - `UC_Comment`: Users can comment on other users' buildings.
  - `UC_SearchBuildings`: All visitors can search for buildings using full-text search.
  - `UC_ReleaseEntry`: Users can make an entry public.
  - `UC_DeleteComment`: Admins can delete comments.
  - `UC_SetUpUser`: Admins set up user accounts.
  - `UC_ActivateUser`: Admins activate user accounts after verification.

- **Generalization**: `Administrator` is a specialized type of `User`.

- **Relationships**:
  - A `WebPortal` contains multiple `Buildings`.
  - A `Building` belongs to one `User`.
  - A `User` can manage multiple `Buildings`.
  - A `Building` can have multiple `Images` and `AdditionalEntries`.

---

### 🧾 **Notes**
- The model is designed to be extensible and supports the described functionality of the web portal.

